description:
&lt;p&gt;This post is fixed term for 6 months due to funding&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic, motivated Registered Nurse to join our dynamic Respiratory Nurse Team on a 6 month fixed term contract. You will be an experienced Registered Nurse who uses specialist skills and knowledge to provide comprehensive care for respiratory patients. This is an ideal opportunity to further your career increasing your skills clinically, professionally and managerially. You will need to demonstrate the ability to lead a clinical workload with a strong emphasis on patient centered care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The base for this post is Withybush General Hospital, Haverfordwest but you may be required to work Health Board wide to support the Respiratory Multi-professional Team. You will be working across a spectrum of respiratory conditions but primarily with patients who have COPD, asthma, bronchiectasis and those requiring acute or home non-invasive ventilation. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You must have excellent communication skills and experience of managing complex and challenging situations and demonstrate clinical judgement and critical decision making skills based upon evidence based practice. This includes holding a caseload for defined episodes of care, and provide advice, education and support to patients, their family and other health care professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to practice clinically in agreed care settings according to established protocols and guidelines, and will contribute to the development and smooth running of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on 23rd November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
